Doc Del,<br><br>
Certainly there are exceptions to every rule. But, my purpose was to attempt to shed some light on what Dana possibly had heard Vietnam Vets say. That is: in comparison to rear units - there was no racism in the combat units.<br><br>
There was racism ( which worked both ways ) that was very evident in the rear.<br><br>
Out in the bush, I witnessed people who came to realize the importance of people as individuals and as members of the unit. I like to think that some of these experiences had positive effects on these soldiers when they returned home.
